[2]
Date: Wed 11 Sep 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ontario Ministry of Health and Long Term Care, Wed 11 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://www.gov.on.ca/health/english/program/pubhealth/wnv_mn.html>


Ontario: West Nile Virus Update
-------------------------------
Humans

As of Wed 11 Sep 2002, there has been one confirmed human case of West Nile
virus in Ontario, in an individual from Halton region. In addition,
confirmatory results are pending for a further 10 probable positive West
Nile virus tests on humans in Ontario; 3 in Halton, 5 in Peel, 1 in Toronto
and 1 in Windsor.

Mosquitoes

As of Wed 11 Sep 2002, 71 pools of mosquitoes collected from 11 regions in
Ontario have tested positive this year.

Birds

As of Wed 11 Sep 2002, the number of birds confirmed West Nile
virus-positive in Ontario this year stands at 234, plus one presumed
positive bird.

