Quebec: West Nile Virus Update
------------------------------
Birds

As of Fri 6 Sep 2002, a total 77 birds have tested West Nile virus-positive
in 8 districts of Quebec in 2002.

Mosquitoes

As of Fri 6 Sep 2002, a total of 4 pools of mosquitoes have tested West
Nile virus-positive in 2 districts of Quebec in 2002.

******
[4]
Date: Wed 11 Sep 2002
From : ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Saskatchewan Health, West Nile virus update, Thu 5 Sep 2002 [edited]
<http://www.health.gov.sk.ca/rr_west_nile_update.html>


Saskatchwan: West Nile Virus Update
-----------------------------------
Birds

The latest tests for West Nile virus in Saskatchewan birds have produced an
additional 14 confirmed positive results. The 14 confirmed positive results
include 9 crows, previously presumed positive, found in Yorkton (5),
Melville, Melville area, Crooked Lake Provincial Park, and Loreburn plus 6
new birds found in Estevan, Kamsack, Perdue, Moose Jaw, St. Gregor, and a
second bird in Regina. There are currently no birds that are presumed
positive. The total number of confirmed West Nile virus-positive birds is
now 21 collected from 13 localities in Saskatchewan.

Equines

[The ProMED-mail post referenced below reported in addition the diagnosis
of West Nile virus infection in 6 equines. It was incorrectly stated in the
Moderator's comment that these were probably the first equines to test
positive in Canada. The above report indicates that equines in Manitoba
have also tested West Nile virus-positive, but details are not given. - Mod.CP]

